1
00:01:01,352 --> 00:01:04,314
Within the hour,
the CCTV system will be reactivated,

2
00:01:04,397 --> 00:01:06,107
along with the compound's roving drones.

3
00:01:06,691 --> 00:01:08,276
By the way, here's what we discussed.

4
00:01:13,573 --> 00:01:14,699
I'm sorry, everyone.

5
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:17,911
I'm sure this wasn't the plot twist
you expected in your lives.

6
00:01:17,994 --> 00:01:20,580
I'm only asking for a little more trust.

7
00:01:20,663 --> 00:01:21,831
Just trust.

8
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:24,709
Even just a little help. Some support.

9
00:01:24,793 --> 00:01:26,628
<i>Just so we can make sure Chiara is safe.</i>

10
00:01:26,711 --> 00:01:28,713
Maybe we won't even need an extraction.

11
00:01:28,797 --> 00:01:33,843
Because you said earlier
your sweetheart would be back soon.

12
00:01:42,101 --> 00:01:43,311
What is that?!

13
00:01:59,744 --> 00:02:02,622
That's what happens when
you don't get enough sleep,

14
00:02:02,705 --> 00:02:04,249
and all you do is work.

15
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:05,667
You're getting paranoid, Bok.

16
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:07,961
Isn't it true that in our line of work,

17
00:02:08,044 --> 00:02:10,672
it's better to overreact
than be over prepared.

18
00:02:11,881 --> 00:02:13,591
Okay, okay. I get it.

19
00:02:13,675 --> 00:02:15,176
But what if?

20
00:02:17,053 --> 00:02:18,471
What if Mikoy is right?

21
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:20,473
That Chiara will come back,

22
00:02:20,557 --> 00:02:23,309
and she will bring something
that we really need,

23
00:02:23,393 --> 00:02:25,353
like, urgently need.

24
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:47,625
I don't have an appetite.

25
00:02:52,881 --> 00:02:54,173
Oh, please!

26
00:02:57,802 --> 00:02:59,554
You can eat here,

27
00:03:00,221 --> 00:03:01,681
but I can't join you.

28
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:04,601
I'm not feeling well.

29
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:16,362
It's just…

30
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:18,156
I'm feeling down.

31
00:03:18,823 --> 00:03:20,658
Feeling down?

32
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:23,119
Yes, "feeling down" in English.

33
00:03:30,668 --> 00:03:32,045
Well, obviously…

34
00:03:32,128 --> 00:03:33,421
La Morte Bianca.

35
00:03:37,967 --> 00:03:39,135
Because…

36
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:41,512
I dreamed about our daughter.

37
00:03:41,596 --> 00:03:44,641
So, what happened in your dream?

38
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:46,601
She came here.

39
00:03:48,144 --> 00:03:52,815
But she was in a hurry,
and she was avoiding La Morte Bianca.

40
00:03:52,899 --> 00:03:54,734
That's why we didn't
get to see each other.

41
00:03:56,903 --> 00:03:58,863
I miss our daughter so much, Viktor.

42
00:04:01,366 --> 00:04:03,117
You're not alone.

43
00:04:10,124 --> 00:04:11,376
For now,

44
00:04:13,044 --> 00:04:15,255
the only thing we can do

45
00:04:16,005 --> 00:04:17,382
is to trust her.

46
00:04:33,940 --> 00:04:38,278
I'm just glad we raised our daughter
to be… brave.

47
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:40,822
Sometimes she's a little too fierce.

48
00:04:40,905 --> 00:04:42,448
It worries me.

49
00:04:43,074 --> 00:04:46,119
Well, she takes after you.

50
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,417
How much is this?

51
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:53,626
Fifty pesos a kilo.

52
00:04:53,710 --> 00:04:55,753
That's too expensive. Make it 20.

53
00:04:55,837 --> 00:04:57,714
Come on, prices
are really high these days.

54
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,924
You should just grow these yourselves.

55
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:01,676
You're such a tough bargainer.

56
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:03,094
Why don't you just ask for it for free?

57
00:05:03,177 --> 00:05:04,721
Why are you butting in?

58
00:05:06,472 --> 00:05:08,016
Serves you right!

59
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:10,143
Sweetheart, you're picking a fight again.

60
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:13,563
- The baby's here, crying nonstop.
- Why did you bring our baby here?

61
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:14,814
Has the baby been crying?

62
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:16,691
- The baby has been looking for you.
- Oh, my poor baby.

63
00:05:16,774 --> 00:05:19,110
Come on, let's go. The poor baby's crying.

64
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,947
Serves you right.

65
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:28,870
The baby's crying.

66
00:05:28,953 --> 00:05:32,123
Oh, no, why is my baby crying?

67
00:05:32,206 --> 00:05:34,542
- You're not having a good daddy.
- Baby's looking for you.

68
00:05:38,713 --> 00:05:39,756
Let's go.

69
00:05:41,132 --> 00:05:42,842
Poor baby.

70
00:05:43,926 --> 00:05:45,303
<i>Oh, Mikoy.</i>

71
00:05:45,386 --> 00:05:47,388
<i>I miss you so much.</i>

72
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,599
<i>I'm coming home, sweetheart.</i>

73
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:27,321
They really are <i>pinagpala</i>.

74
00:07:27,405 --> 00:07:31,075
I'm sorry. Pinagpala means "blessed".

75
00:07:35,621 --> 00:07:39,667
That's why I want you to find them.

76
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:04,775
I mean Chiara too.

77
00:08:52,573 --> 00:08:54,450
Have you all finished eating?

78
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:58,120
Hey, stand up. Let's go.

79
00:09:07,338 --> 00:09:09,048
You know, I think this is the first time

80
00:09:09,131 --> 00:09:12,218
we've had this many people
staying in our safehouse.

81
00:09:12,301 --> 00:09:15,972
Due to this unique situation
that involves national security,

82
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:17,139
we're ready

83
00:09:17,223 --> 00:09:19,308
at the Global Agency
for Government Operations

84
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:22,103
to provide everything you need
while you're here.

85
00:09:22,186 --> 00:09:25,523
Yup. And because of our unique situation,

86
00:09:25,606 --> 00:09:26,983
as Agent Alex said,

87
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:31,028
I'll require all of you
to follow the 5 C's.

88
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:38,536
And above all, consultation.

89
00:09:39,996 --> 00:09:42,498
Yes, Tess. Consultation.

90
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:47,336
Because we're responsible
for everyone's safety.

91
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:48,796
You need to consult us

92
00:09:48,879 --> 00:09:51,382
if you have any major life decisions,

93
00:09:51,465 --> 00:09:52,800
for safety purposes.

94
00:09:53,551 --> 00:09:55,219
So, every time you leave the compound,

95
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:57,888
you must first ask for our permission.

96
00:09:57,972 --> 00:09:59,890
And if there's a valid reason to go out,

97
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:02,351
you can't leave without
someone from the agency.

98
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:04,437
We'll personally escort you.

99
00:10:12,528 --> 00:10:17,199
And never forget, when we say "no",
it's a no.

100
00:10:27,043 --> 00:10:29,170
And here's the one thing
you must never forget.

101
00:10:29,253 --> 00:10:32,923
My favorite house rule
here at the safehouse.

102
00:10:36,927 --> 00:10:39,221
Captain Pepe!
You've been saying "no" this whole time!

103
00:10:44,352 --> 00:10:46,562
And above all, consultation.

104
00:10:48,564 --> 00:10:50,024
That's actually Habit No. 4

105
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:52,568
from <i>The 7 Habits</i>
<i>of Highly Effective People</i>.

106
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:54,737
We have that book here. Just look for it.

107
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,322
Don't be shy to borrow it.

108
00:10:57,448 --> 00:11:00,451
And that's it. I hope
the safehouse rules are clear.

109
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:02,703
And again, this may not be an ideal setup,

110
00:11:02,787 --> 00:11:05,956
but we hope you can still feel at home.

111
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:08,959
All right, thank you very much,
Agents Alex and Sianong.

112
00:11:09,043 --> 00:11:10,002
And…

113
00:11:10,586 --> 00:11:15,257
speaking for my fellow safehouse mates,

114
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:20,012
you can count on us
not to give you any headaches.

115
00:11:20,096 --> 00:11:22,973
Thank you very much,
Mario, Tess, and everyone.

116
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:27,228
Let's get started.

117
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:30,064
Grab the cleaning supplies,
and let's tidy up the house.

118
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:47,540
Welcome, everyone, to Sitio San Juan!

119
00:11:48,374 --> 00:11:51,961
Through our partnership
with Save the Seas International,

120
00:11:52,044 --> 00:11:53,587
we, the residents here,

121
00:11:53,671 --> 00:11:56,590
are delighted to welcome
all of your volunteers.

122
00:12:00,302 --> 00:12:02,304
Thank you too, Captain!

123
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:03,764
Let's give a round of applause

124
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:08,227
to our captain and our foster families
in this volunteer program.

125
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:12,898
Now then, as you indicated
on the forms earlier,

126
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:16,026
we'll start with a short clean-up drive.

127
00:12:26,954 --> 00:12:29,081
Mario, can we do this?

128
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:34,211
We can. Just stay strong.

129
00:12:34,795 --> 00:12:38,674
What I mean is, can we really live here?

130
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,093
It's only temporary.

131
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:46,474
Right? It's a very unique situation
in the interest of national security.

132
00:12:47,016 --> 00:12:48,267
We'll get through it.

133
00:12:50,019 --> 00:12:50,853
You know,

134
00:12:50,936 --> 00:12:54,940
I can adjust
and get along with other people.

135
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:58,527
I'm just worried about Angelito.

136
00:12:59,570 --> 00:13:01,113
He's far away.

137
00:13:01,697 --> 00:13:03,574
He's not here with us.

138
00:13:04,658 --> 00:13:07,119
And aren't cell phones not allowed here?

139
00:13:07,203 --> 00:13:10,456
We don't even know
what's happening outside.

140
00:13:10,539 --> 00:13:13,209
We don't even know what's happening here.

141
00:13:16,128 --> 00:13:19,548
Mario, when will all of this be over?

142
00:13:20,883 --> 00:13:22,009
It feels like…

143
00:13:22,092 --> 00:13:24,678
too many things are happening.

144
00:13:25,262 --> 00:13:29,350
I'm afraid I won't be able to handle it
if something else goes wrong.

145
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:31,852
Everything will become clear
once Chiara arrives.

146
00:13:32,436 --> 00:13:33,521
Are you sure about that?

147
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:42,238
All right, everyone, let's grab
the things we'll be using

148
00:13:42,321 --> 00:13:44,281
to collect the trash out back.

149
00:13:44,365 --> 00:13:48,035
And guys, please be careful
when picking up the trash, okay?

150
00:13:50,955 --> 00:13:51,956
Let's go.

151
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:53,165
Thank you.

152
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:54,166
This way, please.

153
00:13:56,252 --> 00:14:00,381
I'm trying, but
I just can't stop worrying.

154
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:02,591
Why? What happened?

155
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:06,512
It's just that… Mom and Dad
haven't even called or texted me.

156
00:14:07,221 --> 00:14:08,430
Not since yesterday.

157
00:14:08,514 --> 00:14:11,725
Angelito, isn't there
barely any signal here?

158
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:13,978
What did they tell you?

159
00:14:14,061 --> 00:14:16,564
To enjoy yourself here. Right?

160
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:20,901
So you won't just be focused
on school and home.

161
00:14:20,985 --> 00:14:23,571
Come on, stay focused.

162
00:14:27,074 --> 00:14:29,785
Yes, yes. Clear, clear. Let's go!

163
00:14:34,039 --> 00:14:36,250
Here are your gloves.

164
00:14:38,168 --> 00:14:40,129
Honey, I know you have a lot on your mind.

165
00:14:41,088 --> 00:14:42,798
And I understand.

166
00:14:43,591 --> 00:14:45,593
I miss Angelito too.

167
00:14:45,676 --> 00:14:46,927
And I also want…

168
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:50,055
the four of us to be together.

169
00:14:51,181 --> 00:14:52,808
But for now,

170
00:14:52,892 --> 00:14:54,894
this is all we can do.

171
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:57,146
Wait.

172
00:14:58,439 --> 00:15:00,441
And trust each other.

173
00:15:02,318 --> 00:15:03,485
You trust me, don't you?

174
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:05,863
Oh, come on! Of course I do, honey!

175
00:15:11,535 --> 00:15:14,038
To ease your worries,

176
00:15:14,121 --> 00:15:15,831
I have something for you.

177
00:15:17,416 --> 00:15:18,918
But promise you'll take good care of it.

178
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,639
This thing Aling Tess gave me is great.

179
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:35,142
My back and neck finally feel better!

180
00:15:35,976 --> 00:15:37,478
Have you been here long, buddy?

181
00:15:37,561 --> 00:15:38,896
Not that long.

182
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:41,440
I got here not long after Mikoy's group.

183
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:42,942
It's all right here.

184
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:46,111
Buddy.

185
00:15:46,987 --> 00:15:49,448
It's so quiet here.

186
00:15:49,531 --> 00:15:51,450
Unlike back home at our corner.

187
00:15:51,533 --> 00:15:53,160
It's always lively there!

188
00:15:53,243 --> 00:15:56,413
People chatting and cracking
lots of jokes.

189
00:15:56,497 --> 00:15:57,957
I miss gin too.

190
00:15:58,040 --> 00:15:59,249
The gym?

191
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:00,876
I go to the gym. Let's work out together!

192
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:01,919
- Gin.
- Build some muscle.

193
00:16:02,002 --> 00:16:02,836
The drink.

194
00:16:03,754 --> 00:16:04,922
I'm having withdrawal symptoms.

195
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:08,634
You know, you'll eventually get used
to the silence, right?

196
00:16:10,594 --> 00:16:11,637
Buddy.

197
00:16:12,262 --> 00:16:13,222
Let me ask you something.

198
00:16:14,515 --> 00:16:17,476
Do you think Chiara will come back?

199
00:16:18,894 --> 00:16:19,979
I think…

200
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:23,774
she will.

201
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:25,901
She's probably just figuring out
her next move

202
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:27,361
to avoid the syndicate.

203
00:16:27,444 --> 00:16:29,279
After all, they're chasing her.

204
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:32,616
And she's waiting for the right time,
especially since Mikoy is here.

205
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:35,452
I don't think she's coming back.

206
00:16:36,161 --> 00:16:37,746
Even if she loves Mikoy so much,

207
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:39,498
she's not coming back.

208
00:16:39,581 --> 00:16:41,458
She's living in a fancy mansion now,

209
00:16:41,542 --> 00:16:42,876
with a comfortable room

210
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,753
and delicious food.

211
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:46,672
She's not coming back!

212
00:16:48,048 --> 00:16:50,592
You're all grown men,
yet you're such gossips.

213
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:51,927
Get back to cleaning!

214
00:16:56,932 --> 00:16:58,017
Agent Dara, why did you call?

215
00:16:59,935 --> 00:17:01,520
The agency has been looking for you.

216
00:17:02,563 --> 00:17:05,274
Didn't I already tell you
I can't leave yet?

217
00:17:05,899 --> 00:17:10,154
Isn't today the orientation
for the agent applicants?

218
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:12,114
Exactly, I know, but…

219
00:17:20,831 --> 00:17:24,626
Aren't you the one assigned
to conduct today's orientation?

220
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:27,212
<i>So what now?</i>

221
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:32,468
They're going to miss your lecture
on <i>The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People</i>

222
00:17:33,135 --> 00:17:35,888
<i>and your trivia</i>

223
00:17:35,971 --> 00:17:38,348
about <i>The Lord of the Rings</i>,

224
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:40,934
including your favorite quote
from the trilogy.

225
00:17:43,854 --> 00:17:47,775
Agent Dara, I know what you're doing.

226
00:17:51,361 --> 00:17:54,073
<i>No, I can't. I can't leave this place.</i>

227
00:17:54,656 --> 00:17:57,534
Chiara still hasn't returned
to the safe house.

228
00:17:57,618 --> 00:18:00,579
If I leave, who knows
what might happen here?

229
00:18:01,789 --> 00:18:07,669
What you really mean is,
you're afraid to be away from Agent Alex.

230
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:15,094
What?

231
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:16,220
You.

232
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:18,472
I am only doing my job here.

233
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:20,390
You're reading too much into it, okay?

234
00:18:20,474 --> 00:18:24,186
It's just work, nothing personal.
No flirting, just work.

235
00:18:24,269 --> 00:18:25,646
All right, bye.

236
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:48,168
- Hi, Mom!
- Good morning.

237
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:49,628
Looking good!

238
00:18:50,754 --> 00:18:51,755
- Mom.
- Hmm?

239
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:53,632
How's Angelito doing?

240
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:57,803
Is he doing okay with that community work?

241
00:18:57,886 --> 00:19:00,514
Yes, he's doing just fine.

242
00:19:00,597 --> 00:19:03,225
At least he's with his friends, right?

243
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:06,895
Yes, but what happens
when his volunteer work is over?

244
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,772
He won't have a home to return to.

245
00:19:09,314 --> 00:19:11,066
Poor Angelito.

246
00:19:11,150 --> 00:19:13,277
He still doesn't know our house is gone.

247
00:19:19,992 --> 00:19:21,743
Mom! That's not allowed!

248
00:19:23,162 --> 00:19:24,454
You really are something!

249
00:19:24,538 --> 00:19:26,790
They just went over the safehouse rules!

250
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:31,670
I'm a mother. I can't bear
to be without my youngest!

251
00:19:33,005 --> 00:19:34,256
Mom!

252
00:19:34,882 --> 00:19:36,550
How did you even get that in here?

253
00:19:37,384 --> 00:19:41,054
Your father found a way to sneak it in.

254
00:19:41,638 --> 00:19:43,640
I knew it!

255
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:45,893
Dad is such a troublemaker!

256
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:47,269
A troublemaker.

257
00:19:47,352 --> 00:19:49,521
That's where you got it from!

258
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:51,356
Besides, your father said

259
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,233
I should keep this safe.

260
00:19:54,193 --> 00:19:56,653
But yes, I know it's not allowed.

261
00:19:56,737 --> 00:20:00,574
You never know
when we might need it, right?

262
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:02,576
But it really isn't allowed.

263
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:05,746
I just got in trouble
for breaking the rules.

264
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:08,373
If Agent Alex or Agent Sianong finds out,

265
00:20:08,457 --> 00:20:10,834
oh, no, I'll really be in trouble, Mom.

266
00:20:12,711 --> 00:20:15,881
Honey, just let me handle this.

267
00:20:16,757 --> 00:20:19,009
I promise I won't drag you into it.

268
00:20:19,092 --> 00:20:20,260
I promise!

269
00:20:20,344 --> 00:20:23,347
If we get caught,
I'll be the only one who gets scolded.

270
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:27,726
You have to understand.

271
00:20:27,809 --> 00:20:32,022
I'm only keeping this
to give myself some peace of mind.

272
00:20:32,105 --> 00:20:34,608
Just think about it.

273
00:20:34,691 --> 00:20:37,361
If La Morte Bianca

274
00:20:37,444 --> 00:20:42,449
could blow up our house
and our bakery,

275
00:20:42,532 --> 00:20:45,744
then they could blow up any place here,

276
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:47,996
any island, right?

277
00:21:06,848 --> 00:21:08,558
Not our house!

278
00:21:09,142 --> 00:21:10,310
Run!

279
00:21:10,394 --> 00:21:11,520
Sis!

280
00:21:13,021 --> 00:21:13,981
No, please!

281
00:21:14,064 --> 00:21:15,732
Not me!

282
00:21:17,234 --> 00:21:18,610
Move!

283
00:21:24,241 --> 00:21:25,534
Negative here, ma'am.

284
00:21:26,285 --> 00:21:27,744
What we're looking for isn't here.

285
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:37,129
Search inside too!

286
00:21:37,838 --> 00:21:38,922
Copy, boss!

287
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:40,841
You, over there!

288
00:21:59,776 --> 00:22:01,737
In Sitio San Juan.

289
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:04,448
You know, it's surrounded by islands.

290
00:22:06,616 --> 00:22:07,826
SAN JUAN GROUP OF ISLANDS

291
00:22:17,461 --> 00:22:18,879
I heard it's beautiful there!

292
00:22:18,962 --> 00:22:20,213
But it's far away,

293
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:23,133
and the signal is weak!

294
00:22:23,925 --> 00:22:28,221
But of course, I'm still hoping
he'll send a text or give me a call.

295
00:22:28,305 --> 00:22:29,723
Right? You're his brother.

296
00:22:29,806 --> 00:22:32,642
Wouldn't it be better
if he could come here?

297
00:22:32,726 --> 00:22:33,560
Right?

298
00:22:36,563 --> 00:22:40,442
There's still trash over here.
Don't forget the others.

299
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:42,527
- Hey!
- You might don't get it.

300
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:43,487
Hey!

301
00:22:43,570 --> 00:22:44,446
Hey!

302
00:22:44,529 --> 00:22:45,614
Angelito!

303
00:22:45,697 --> 00:22:48,867
You know,
you've been on your phone all day.

304
00:22:48,950 --> 00:22:49,785
If I were you,

305
00:22:50,494 --> 00:22:52,204
I'd just enjoy the view.

306
00:22:52,829 --> 00:22:53,997
- Right?
- Come on, Angelito.

307
00:22:54,081 --> 00:22:56,666
Your parents are probably just busy
at your cake shop.

308
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,626
Just let them be for now.

309
00:22:57,709 --> 00:23:00,670
Enjoy the view and let's get cleaning.

310
00:23:01,505 --> 00:23:02,631
Luisa!

311
00:23:04,841 --> 00:23:06,593
I feel guilty again, Mom.

312
00:23:07,469 --> 00:23:11,389
Angelito should've been enjoying college
and living his life as a college student.

313
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:13,767
Instead, one trial after another.

314
00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:16,728
And now, all of you
are caught up in it too.

315
00:23:18,855 --> 00:23:19,898
Honey.

316
00:23:19,981 --> 00:23:21,441
Come on.

317
00:23:21,525 --> 00:23:24,361
You never wanted any of this.

318
00:23:25,403 --> 00:23:28,532
And even though Angelito is young,

319
00:23:28,615 --> 00:23:31,201
he'll understand.

320
00:23:32,869 --> 00:23:34,621
This isn't your fault, sweetheart.

321
00:23:47,384 --> 00:23:48,426
Luisa!

322
00:23:52,222 --> 00:23:53,640
- Angelito!
- Hey!

323
00:23:53,723 --> 00:23:55,642
- What are you doing?
- Why do you have to climb there?

324
00:23:55,725 --> 00:23:57,978
- What are you doing?
- Hey!

325
00:23:58,061 --> 00:23:59,646
I'm looking for a signal.

326
00:23:59,729 --> 00:24:01,523
- Come down from there.
- Why?

327
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:02,774
I'm getting a signal up here.

328
00:24:02,858 --> 00:24:04,776
- You might get yourself hurt.
- There… There's a…

329
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:10,615
SAN JUAN GROUP OF ISLANDS

330
00:24:34,222 --> 00:24:35,557
<i>Where are Mom and Dad?</i>

331
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:38,476
<i>Aunt Tess doesn't have an appetite.</i>

332
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:40,312
How's she feeling?

333
00:24:40,395 --> 00:24:41,605
How about Dad? Why is he not here as well?

334
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:44,858
Looks like they have to decompress?

335
00:24:45,525 --> 00:24:46,610
Just hold on, Mom.

336
00:24:46,693 --> 00:24:48,987
We will eventually end
the force of the syndicate,

337
00:24:49,070 --> 00:24:50,780
<i>especially that La Morte Bianca.</i>

338
00:24:53,241 --> 00:24:54,409
<i>Tell me the truth.</i>

339
00:24:54,993 --> 00:24:58,330
<i>Daddy Sir, what is happening</i>
<i>to the Pinagpalas?</i>

340
00:24:58,413 --> 00:25:00,874
Why is their bakery temporarily closed?

341
00:25:00,957 --> 00:25:02,375
Are they okay?

342
00:25:06,087 --> 00:25:07,297
What's that?

343
00:25:08,506 --> 00:25:10,842
- Cover.
- Get down! Cover! I said move!

344
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:12,510
What's happening?

345
00:25:12,594 --> 00:25:15,430
- Why is there an alarm?
- Mikoy, take cover!

346
00:25:15,513 --> 00:25:16,765
- Wait a minute!
- Mom.

347
00:25:17,390 --> 00:25:18,266
Wait!

348
00:25:18,350 --> 00:25:19,809
<i>Mikoy, what are you doing?!</i>
